{"key":"post-9431482","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9431482</id>\n<content>Mist the substrate trays and/or cakes, whether they're cased or not, and the perlite.&amp;nbsp; Of course some is going to get on the walls of the FC and it helps.&amp;nbsp; However, the perlite has a million or more times the surface area of the walls, so that's where you want your moisture going so it can do some good.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;My point is that to mist the walls &lt;i&gt;only&lt;/i&gt; per the advice of hundreds of posts here that parrot previous bad advice is flat out wrong.&amp;nbsp; If you're giving proper air exchange, your substrate &lt;i&gt;will&lt;/i&gt; dry out, even if you have 99% humidity.&amp;nbsp; Therefore, you need to mist to make up for the lost moisture.&amp;nbsp; This wetting, and then drying between mist cycles is a major pinning trigger.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9432037</next>\n<prev>9431439</prev>\n<first>9429286</first>\n<last>9439075</last>\n<when>1229299390</when>\n<utime>12/15/08 02:03 AM</utime>\n</post>"}